The Ondo state governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, has emerged winner in the primary of the All Progressives Congress (APC) held on Monday in Akure, the state capital. With the result announced so far, Akeredolu is leading other aspirants in all the 18 local government of the state with a wide margin. Governor Akeredolu will represent the party in the October 10 governorship election in the state. Details later…